The consistent 2-configuration requires each element to appear in exactly one cell (order 1) and there is exactly one cell of size 2, so the set must have exactly 2 elements, giving n=2 and k=n+5=7. For the best-of-9 series, exactly 7 games occur if after 6 games one team has 4 wins and the other 2, and the leading team wins game 7. With win probability p=2/3, the total probability is C(6,4)p^5(1-p)^2 + C(6,2)p^2(1-p)^5 = 15*(32/243)*(1/9) + 15*(4/9)*(1/243) = 540/2187 = 20/81.

